 Mathematics and Industrial Engineering of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.polymtl.ca\/\">Polytechnique Montreal<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cirrelt.ca\/\">CIRRELT<\/a> under the supervision of <a href=\"https:\/\/scholar.google.ca\/citations?user=CilK624AAAAJ&amp;hl=en\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/scholar.google.ca\/citations?user=CilK624AAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Prof. Michel Gendreau<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/scholar.google.ca\/citations?user=C_zcTIAAAAAJ&amp;hl\">Prof. Teodor Crainic<\/a>. I received my Ph.D. degree in Industrial Engineering and Operations Management from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ku.edu.tr\/en\/\">Koc University<\/a>. <\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>My current research interest falls into two broad topics: <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>1- Using ML and optimization methods for practical applications, including last-mile and middle-mile logistics, production scheduling, and power distribution systems.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>2- Leveraging AI to enhance optimization methods, including using ML to improve heuristics and branch-and-bound, and applying LLMs for optimization modeling and interpretable OR.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I am an Operations Research scientist with a decade of experience in algorithm design (meta\/heuristic, exact optimization) and machine learning methods to solve challenging business problems. Currently, I am a Staff Scientist at the Huawei Vancouver Research Center and the AI Lead for the Huawei Optimization Solver (OptVers). I am responsible for directing research efforts [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_coblocks_attr":"","_coblocks_dimensions":"","_coblocks_responsive_height":"","_coblocks_accordion_ie_support":"","footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/21"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"